<HEAD>Northeast Shivers; Clear Skies Over Much of Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Cold winds and clear skies helped chill the Northeast early
today, while fair skies covered much of the nation.
   Warnings for frost and freezing temperatures overnight were
posted over much of southern New England, southeast and
north-central New York, much of Pennsylvania, northern Ohio and
parts of West Virginia.
   On Wednesday, showers were scattered from southwest Montana
across western Wyoming, eastern Idaho and northern Utah and over
central Colorado. Rain also fell along the lower Texas Gulf Coast,
over Florida and from southeast Georgia to the southern coast of
South Carolina.
   A thunderstorm over Twin Falls, Idaho, brought flooding and
small hail. Thunderstorm winds gusted to near 50 mph at Salt Lake
City and to 58 mph at Cody, Wyo.
   Lakeland, Fla., reached 94 degrees, breaking their high for the
date. The nation's hottest spots Wednesday were Borrego Springs,
Calif., and Gila Bend and Yuma, Ariz., all recording 107 degrees.
   Reports around the country at 3 a.m. included:
   EAST: Albany, N.Y., 34 fair; Atlanta 61 cloudy; Boston 44 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 62 cloudy; Chattanooga 60 fair; Cincinnati 43
fair; Cleveland 42 fair; Detroit 41 fair; Hatteras 64 windy;
Jacksonville 76 showery; Key West 85 windy; Knoxville 56 fair;
Macon 64 cloudy; Miami 83 fair; New York 46 fair; Philadelphia 45
fair; Pittsburgh 39 fair; Portland, Maine, 35 fair; Richmond 45
fair; Tampa 77 fair; Washington, D.C., 49 fair.
   CENTRAL: Birmingham 65 cloudy; Bismarck 60 partly cloudy;
Chicago 49 fair; Denver 58 fair; Des Moines 45 fair; Indianapolis
44 fair; Kansas City 51 fair; Little Rock 61 partly cloudy;
Louisville 48 fair; Memphis 65 cloudy; Nashville 55 fair; New
Orleans 71 cloudy; North Platte 59 fair; Oklahoma City 54 fair;
Omaha 47 fair; Rapid City 68 partly cloudy; St. Louis 53 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 59 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 40 fair; San Antonio
63 fair.
   WEST: Albuquerque 61 fair; Anchorage 41 partly cloudy; Boise 65
cloudy; Casper 53 fair; Fairbanks 40 fair; Great Falls 50 fair;
Honolulu 78 fair; Las Vegas 74 fair; Los Angeles 67 fair; Medford
57 fair; Pendleton 57 fair; Phoenix 86 fair; Portland, Ore., 60
fair; Reno 57 partly cloudy; Salt Lake City 61 fair; San Diego 68
fair; San Francisco 56 fair; Seattle 56 foggy; Spokane 53 fair.
   INTERNATIONAL: Montreal 43 cloudy; Ottawa 37 fair; Regina 48
fair; Toronto 37 fair; Winnipeg 61 fair.
</TEXT>
