<HEAD>Mason Out of Giuliani Campaign After Remark About Dinkins</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Comic Jackie Mason says he was just joking, but
he agreed to stop mayoral campaigning after saying Democratic
candidate David Dinkins looks like ``a black model without a job''
and claiming Jews will vote for him out of guilt.
   The remarks, published Wednesday in The Village Voice, ended
Mason's affiliation with the campaign of Republican mayoral
candidate Rudolph Giuliani.
   ``Mason is withdrawing from the campaign because he didn't want
this matter to deflect from the importance of the campaign,'' said
Charles Perkins, a Giuliani spokesman. Perkins said Giuliani was
``troubled'' by Mason's remarks.
   At a news conference, Mason tried to show he is not racist by
producing a $100 canceled check he sent to the NAACP in 1988 and
having a black agent, Jim Willis, attest that Mason had hired a
number of black singers for his shows.
   As for his remark that Dinkins looks like a model, Mason said:
``I don't think a joke like that means anything. I said much worse
jokes about Jews.''
   He said he supports Giuliani because ``he's a great crimefighter
and blacks are suffering from crime more than anyone else. I wanted
him to help the minorities and the poor of this city, so now all of
a sudden they call me a racist.''
   Dinkins said he was ``not particularly'' offended by the remarks
but added, ``I can say that that kind of comment is not helpful to
our city.''
   Mayor Edward I. Koch, who lost the primary to Dinkins, and a
number of leading Jewish organizations issued statements denouncing
Mason's remarks.
   Mason also was quoted by the Voice as having said: ``There is a
sick Jewish problem of voting for a black man no matter how unfit
he is for the job. ... Jews are sick with complexes.'' He later
called that remark ``stupid.''
   The comedian said he was ``exaggerating to prove a point'' when
asked to comment on his remark that ``the Jews are constantly
giving millions of dollars to the black people. Have you ever heard
of a black person giving a quarter to a Jew?''
