<DATELINE>DRAGUIGNAN, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of riot police armed with
tear gas took control of a prison in southern France on Thursday
after a night of rioting by inmates protesting prison conditions,
police said.
   Prisoners offered no resistence when about 400 police entered
the jail at 7:45 a.m. and ordered the inmates back to their cells,
according to police.
