demanding higher wages. About 200 prisoners trashed cells, burned
beds and climbed on the roof to protest conditions and the
disruption of visiting schedules caused by the strike.
   Tension is said to be high in many of the country's 180 prisons.
Union officials say guards are on strike in about 70 of them.
