<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--ChickenSlick     09-28 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Chicken Slick,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>Truck Spills Chicken Grease Over 35 Miles of Highway</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GAINESVILLE, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chicken grease that leaked from a truck
smeared over 35 miles of highway, causing several accidents and
slightly injuring a motorist.
   ``It was very slick, mixed with rain _ like ice,'' police
Officer Chris Robinson said.
   The truck was hauling chicken waste from a poultry company
Tuesday, when a valve was left open by mistake, said Sam McClure, a
state maintenance engineer.
   Authorities would not identify the truck's owner, but said the
goo was smeared intermittently over 35 miles. Sand was spread over
the grease.
   Judy Croy of Gainesville was injured slightly when the pickup
truck she was driving hit a greasy patch and struck a guardrail,
Robinson said.
   The Florida Department of Transportation had not determined if
charges against the truck's owner were in order, McClure said.
</TEXT>
