<FIRST>r a AM-CinetexAwards     09-28 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Cinetex Awards,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Awards for Comedy Films at Vegas Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAS VEGAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Movies from the United States, Great Britain,
Hungary, Italy and Hong Kong won top awards at the closing
ceremonies of the Cinetex International Comedy Film Festival.
   The British film, ``The Tall Guy,'' captured best film honors
Wednesday night.
   Film critic Ron Holloway, chairman of the Cinetex awards panel,
said the choice was unanimous.
   ``The Tall Guy'' stars Jeff Goldblum as an American actor
struggling to find success in London.
   Hong Kong actor Michael Hui won best actor honors for his role
in ``Chicken and Duck Talk.''
   American newcomer Maggie Jakobson won best actress honors for
her role in ``New Year's Day.''
   Italy's Maurizio Nichetti earned best director award for ``The
Icicle Thief.''
   ``My 20th Century'' won a special citation for director Ildiko
Enyedi of Hungary.
   Actor George Segal and writer-director-actors Paul Bartel, Paul
Mazursky and Harold Ramis received special awards during the
six-day festival.
</TEXT>
