<TEXT>
   Bush administration officials
apologized for federal drug policy coordinator William Bennett's
dismissive assessment of governors' remarks at the education
summit, Gov. Terry Branstad said Thursday.
   ``A number of (administration) people expressed regret that the
secretary was somewhat flip in his remarks,'' said Branstad,
