<HEAD>Bush Speaks to Principals of America's Best Schools</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush returned from his education
summit on Thursday to a ceremony on the White House lawn and
praised principals from 218 of ``America's best'' schools.
   Bush spoke briefly to the principals from the award-winning
schools after stepping from his helicopter, concluding his
participation in the two-day summit in Charlottesville, Va.
