private, some are religiously affiliated, some are public ... But
you all have one thing in common: a determination to excel.''
   The public and private secondary school winners were named last
May by Education Secretary Lauro F. Cavazos, who said the 218
schools were ``examples of what's right with American education.''
   The schools are located in 42 statres, the District of Colombia
and Peurto Rico.
