<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Amtrak Trail Derails After Hitting Fire Truck</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CALVERTON, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A southbound Amtrak train derailed and a
number of passengers were injured when the train smashed into a
fire truck at a crossing Thursday night, officials said.
   The Crescent, bound from New York to Atlanta and New Orleans,
struck the truck about 7:40 p.m. near this northern Virginia town,
said Amtrak spokesman John Jacobsen.
   Jacobsen said ``numerous cars derailed.'' He said the number of
injured passengers was not immediately known, although Dale
Jefferies, night supervisor at Fauquier Hospital in nearby
Warrenton, said the hospital ``would be receiving some patients.''
   Jacobsen said he did not know if anyone on the fire truck was
hurt.
   The train was carrying 379 passengers and a crew of 20, he said.
   No further details were immediately available.

