<HEAD>Yields on Four-Year Bills Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on four-year Treasury notes rose in
Wednesday's auction to the highest level since last March.
   The average yield was 8.35 percent, up from 8.19 percent at the
last auction on June 28.
   It was the highest rate since four-year notes averaged 9.70
percent on March 29. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of
8\ percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,966.60.
   A total of $7.79 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$21.68 billion.
