   Borden, which has claimed to be the biggest dairy in the world,
hasn't been losing money in dairy, Ventres said, adding ``We're
just not making the money we want.'' It wasn't immediately known
whether Borden will lose its No.1 ranking.
   Borden's program will reduce its worldwide employment by about
7,000 from the present 46,000.
   Ventres said the goal of the consolidation in dairy and its
other planned moves is to make Borden a lowest-cost producer in
each of its six main businesses by 1992.
