<FIRST>r f BC-Kraft-CEO     09-28 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Kraft-CEO,0169</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kraft Names New Chief Executive</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John Richman, who unsuccessfully fought the
takeover of Kraft Inc. by Philip Morris Cos., is retiring as
Kraft's chief executive officer at the end of the year.
   Richman, 62, will be replaced by Michael Miles, currently
president and chief operating officer of Kraft General Foods,
created early last year after the $12 billion takeover.
   Miles, 49, who like Richman will also serve as vice chairman of
Philip Morris, said he expected a smooth transition to occur.
   ``I've worked with John for six or seven years,'' Miles said.
``It's business as usual.''
   Miles will assume his new position immediately. Richman will
remain chairman of Glenview-based Kraft and vice chairman of Philip
Morris until his retirement at the end of the year.
   Richman, whose retirement was previously announced by New
York-based Philip Morris, will join the New York law firm of
Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen &amp; Katz, which specializes in mergers and
acquisitions.
</TEXT>
