<FIRST>r f BC-GMLayoffs     09-28 0151</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-GM Layoffs,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>GM Extends Pickup Plant Down Time</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAYTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Continued slow sales of Chevrolet pickup
trucks will add another week's layoff to the two-week shutdown at
the General Motors Corp. Moraine assembly plant.
   A company spokesman said Wednesday the previously announced
layoff of 2,500 workers will be extended until Oct. 23. The plant
makes Chevrolet S-10 and S-15 pickup trucks.
   ``It is strictly an inventory adjustent. In looking at the sales
picture, they decided to go to three weeks because of (slow) 1989
sales,'' said GM spokesman Tom Klipstine.
   In addition to the Moraine plant, GM's other two light-truck
assembly plants in Pontiac, Mich., and Shreveport, La., will close
for three weeks because of slow sales, he said.
   Through Sept. 20, sales of S-10 pickups were down 4.8 percent to
180,283 and sales of S-15 pickups were off 0.6 percent to 40,473,
according to GM figures.
