<HEAD>London Shares Close Sharply Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: New thruout to UPDATE with close, comments. No pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell sharply in thin trading
Thursday, pushed down by fears that British interest rates will
rise.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 39.5
points, or 1.7 percent, to 2,291.7, the lowest close since July 27
when the index ended at 2,283.7.
   The Financial Times 30-share index finished 31.2 points lower at
1,876.2. The Financial Times 500-share index fell 19.74 points to
close at 1,284.24.
   Volume was a light 403.5 million shares, down from 428.9 million
shares.
   Dealers said shares declined throughout the session on investor
worries that British interest rates would need to be pushed higher
soon to shore up the sagging pound.
   The pound has been weak since Tuesday when the government
reported Britain's third-worst trade deficit for a single month.
