<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
228,203 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
230,189, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 239,374 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 149,601 cars this week,
compared with 152,335 a week ago and 156,445 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 78,602,
compared with last week's 77,854 and last year's 82,929.
   Canadian automakers were to build 22,645 cars this week, up from
22,130 a week ago and from last year's 20,787.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 20,557,
compared with 20,703 a week ago and 20,225 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
