<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 2pm,0286</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices turned upward today in buying
encouraged by the market's recent resilience in the face of
negative news.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 10.83 to 2,683.89
by 2 p.m. on Wall Street.
   Gainers outnumbered losers by about 4 to 3 in nationwide trading
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 774 up, 578 down and
511 unchanged.
   In Wednesday's trading the market was confronted with a drop in
the dollar, higher interest rates, and word from International
Business Machines that its third-quarter earnings would fall well
short of analysts' estimates.
   But stocks bounced back from an early decline to finish mixed,
impressing many observers.
   If that combination of events failed to send prices lower,
traders reasoned, the market might be ready for a rally.
   Meanwhile, interest rates levelled off in the credit markets,
showing little change in today's trading.
   IBM shares, down 6 on Wednesday, dropped another 2| to 108~ as
the most active Big Board issue today.
   AVX jumped 7} to 29]. The company agreed to be acquired by
Japan's Kyocera Corp. through an exchange of stock. Kyocera's
American depositary shares rose [ to 80|.
   L.A. Gear dropped 1| to 43{. The company reported sharply higher
profits for its latest fiscal quarter, but some traders evidently
took profits on that widely anticipated news.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
.84 to 192.66. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up 1.83 at 384.87.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 110.72 million shares with two
hours to go.
