<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Total crude runs to stills averaged 13,747,000
barrels daily during the week ended Friday, Sept. 22, the American
Petroleum Institute reported Thursday. This compared with
13,800,000 barrels daily in the previous week and 12,790,000
barrels daily a year ago.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 11,177,000 barrels daily
compared with 11,228,000 the previous week and 10,134,000 a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the last week amounted to
7,264,000 barrels a day, compared with 7,132,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 6,987,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 6,086,000 a day
compared with 5,890,000 a day last week and 5,684,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
219,993,000 barrels, versus 218,615,000 a week earlier and
218,545,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 191,837,000
barrels compared with 189,490,000 in the previous week and
188,650,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production
for the week ended Friday was 7,540,000 barrels compared with
7,895,000 last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 330,897,000 barrels at the close of
last week, against 328,959,000 a week previous and 318,827,000 a
year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 254,560,000 barrels,
compared with 255,434,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 5,360,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 456,000,
distillate fuel oil, 273,O00, and others 1,052,000, a total of
7,141,000 barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 294,000 barrels, and products
54,000, a total of 348,000 barrels, for a grand total of 7,489,000.
   For the four weeks, daily imports east of California were crude
oil 5,906,000 barrels, residual fuel oil 207,000, distillate fuel
oil 137,000, and others 617,000, for a total of 6,867,000 barrels.
   For the four weeks, California daily imports averaged for crude
oil 364,000 barrels, products 57,000, a total of 421,000 barrels,
for a grand total of 7,288,000.
   The following table shows comparative daily production of the
other principal refined products for the U.S. as a whole and east
of California. Also shown are the comparative stock totals for
certain refined products.
