<FIRST>r f BC-KodakReorganization     09-28 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Kodak Reorganization,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kodak Reorganizing Health and Information Operations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eastman Kodak Co. said Thursday it will
reorganize its health and information units in an effort to cut
costs and streamline operations.
   Officials said four Kodak units, including Sterling Drug, will
be brought together into a new health group. Other Kodak units in
the group will be Health Sciences, Clinical Products and Lehn &amp;
Fink Products.
   Two other new groups, Imaging Information Systems and Commercial
Systems, will combine Kodak operations with common technologies and
customer bases, Kodak President Kay R. Whitmore said.
   The reorganization ``is expected to produce some savings,''
Kodak spokesman Ron Roberts said, but did not elaborate.
   He said the reorganization did not involve any job cuts.
   Last month, Kodak announced it would reduce its workforce by
4,500 jobs worldwide, divest some businesses and change the way
workers and managers are paid. The announcement followed a 60
percent drop in profits in Kodak's second quarter.
